-protocol allowing resources on one site to be accessed by another site, without providing passwords
-Works over HTTP, provides Access Token to 3rd party enabling limited access to data.

Protocol Flow
  Resource Owner: The end user that is allowing access to personal information.
  Client: The application that is requesting access to personal information.
  Authorization Server: Authenticates user and issues JWT access token.
  Resource Server: The server that has the protected resources.

